A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 50-14-1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 meetings open to the public, limitation on action to contest agency action, recording, notice
3 of time and place, access to minutes, and teleconferences, so as to authorize county and
4 regional library boards to conduct meetings via teleconference; to provide for related matters;
5 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 50-14-1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to meetings open
9 to the public, limitation on action to contest agency action, recording, notice of time and
10 place, access to minutes, and teleconferences, is amended by revising subsection (h) as
11 follows:
12 "(h)(1) The following bodies and committees thereof shall be authorized to conduct
13 meetings by teleconference, provided that any such meeting shall be considered to be
14 conducted in compliance with this chapter so long as the notice required by this chapter
15 is provided and, if fewer than a quorum of the members of a body or committee thereof
